OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FJamaica bans music and TV  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fglorifying crime           
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Jamaica's broadcasting authority has   
OL,6, banned content that "glorifies illegal 
OL,7, activity" - such as drug and gun use.  
OL,9,FThe new rules cover TV and radio -     
OL,10,Fincluding music - and list specific    
OL,11,Ftopics that are off-limits.            
OL,13,FScamming, drug abuse and the illegal   
OL,14,Fuse of firearms cannot be "promoted" - 
OL,15,Fand swearing or "near-sounding"        
OL,16,Freplacements are also banned.          
OL,18,FBut the strict nature of the ban has   
OL,19,Fbeen criticised by some artists who    
OL,20,Fargue music is a reflection of life.   
